1
00:00:04,100 --> 00:00:06,910
Episode 16

2
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:52,570
I'm sorry, Ian.

3
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:56,810
I'm sorry.

4
00:01:02,540 --> 00:01:05,640
Conductor Song

5
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:08,840
Mom

6
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:11,600
My Yi Yeong
My hyeong

7
00:01:15,370 --> 00:01:18,200
My Yi Yeong

8
00:01:23,140 --> 00:01:27,050
Let's ride the cable car tomorrow morning, Hong Yi Yeong

9
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:34,760
If you don't answer before I count to three, then you're going.  One, two, three!

10
00:01:37,860 --> 00:01:41,150
I'll call you when I'm in front of your house tomorrow.

11
00:01:41,150 --> 00:01:46,250
- Doesn't she get mad when you do that?
- She does get mad.  She's scary when she gets mad.

12
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:53,200
No, she's not that scary.  If you get to know her, she doesn't really get mad.

13
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:57,240
What are you saying? Is she pretty?

14
00:01:57,240 --> 00:02:00,160
Yes. In my eyes.

15
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:10,950
Conductor Song; Mom; My Hong Yi Yeong; My hyung

16
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:24,400
- Excuse me?
- The card has insufficient funds.

17
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:27,230
Ah, I'm sorry.

18
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:35,510
Please use this to ring it up along with mine.  I'll have an ice coffee.

19
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:47,710
How's your neck?

20
00:02:47,710 --> 00:02:50,290
It's better.

21
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:54,440
How is your uncle doing?

22
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:59,360
It was appendicitis. He had surgery yesterday.

23
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:07,120
Doesn't it seem like we haven't seen each other in a million years, even though we met yesterday?

24
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:19,850
I'm sorry, I have to get going first.

25
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:31,500
Yu Da:  You're a coward hiding anonymously. Aren't you a coward to cheat behind people's back?

26
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:35,830
Would you please respond without hiding: Stand tall.

27
00:03:35,830 --> 00:03:39,330
You're the Conductor's poodle, aren't you?

28
00:03:45,540 --> 00:03:47,610
Good morning.

29
00:03:49,970 --> 00:03:53,360
Shall we start rehearsal?

30
00:03:59,810 --> 00:04:04,280
What's wrong with the mood? You don't want to rehearse?

31
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:14,910
I'm sorry, but I wish you would say something before we start rehearsal.

32
00:04:14,910 --> 00:04:17,980
The bulletin board is bit noisy, as well.

33
00:04:17,980 --> 00:04:23,450
What about the bulletin board?  Are you talking about that picture?

34
00:04:23,450 --> 00:04:29,380
What's the problem with that?  None of you here must be in a relationship?

35
00:04:29,380 --> 00:04:36,850
I don't know why I should explain my personal life in detail, but if you all want me to, well.

36
00:04:36,850 --> 00:04:46,230
The scene in the picture that's on the bulletin board is me thanking Hong Yi Yeong for sending my grandmother, who raised me, a video of myself.

37
00:04:46,230 --> 00:04:52,650
And you are all mistaken about something.  Hong Yi Yeong has no interest in me.

38
00:04:52,650 --> 00:04:55,250
It's the opposite.

39
00:04:58,650 --> 00:05:01,830
I'm interested in her.

40
00:05:08,130 --> 00:05:13,080
Shall we start our practice now?  Hungarian Symphony No. 5 from the first measure.

41
00:05:32,050 --> 00:05:34,510
Ha Eun Ju!

42
00:05:37,570 --> 00:05:42,820
Why did you call me? Does it feel good to get revenge?

43
00:05:42,820 --> 00:05:45,700
If you're talking about Jae Hyeong, it's not like that.

44
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:50,400
I'm sorry, but I don't care if Maestro Nam says that he's interested in you.

45
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:56,860
It's not just once or twice for Maestro Nam's doing as he pleases.

46
00:05:56,860 --> 00:06:00,990
I've suffered enough from his fickleness.

47
00:06:02,060 --> 00:06:05,940
I'm sure that you'll think that I'm being fake, but I'm still going to say it.

48
00:06:05,940 --> 00:06:11,570
The Conductor and I have no relationship at all.  And the Conductor is not being sincere right now.

49
00:06:11,570 --> 00:06:17,000
So what?  If you say it's not so, then does it change what just happened?

50
00:06:18,890 --> 00:06:23,540
Just know this.  Maestro Nam is not the person you know.

51
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:27,470
He's a person who can do anything in order to possess something.

52
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:32,410
He might be someone who could kill a person.

53
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:38,950
He doesn't suit you.

54
00:06:57,450 --> 00:06:59,970
What happened?

55
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:04,860
- What are you talking about?
- You and Ha Eun Ju just now.

56
00:07:04,860 --> 00:07:07,340
Don't concern yourself about it.

57
00:07:08,790 --> 00:07:12,980
Yi Yeong, you don't care if you keep hearing these things?

58
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:24,950
The Conductor says whatever he wants in front of everyone.

59
00:07:26,150 --> 00:07:31,310
Don't stand still for it in the future!  You don't care if people keep calling you a poodle?

60
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:42,270
Do I look alright?

61
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:49,630
- Well, that's not what I was saying.
- Then what is it?

62
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:55,750
- Are you saying it on purpose to upset me?
- What?

63
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:58,660
It's hard for me too.

64
00:07:58,660 --> 00:08:05,270
Not being able to be with you is hard to bear, and the Conductor's jokes are hard to bear.

65
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:08,970
Being attacked by people I don't know is hard to bear also.

66
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:15,100
I'm just enduring it because I have no choice.

67
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:22,560
Whenever you're like this, Yun, I can't really understand you.

68
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:28,730
It's not like you can do anything for me.  What do you want me to do?

69
00:08:32,920 --> 00:08:36,480
What do you want from me?

70
00:08:40,260 --> 00:08:43,960
You probably want me to finish what I need to do, then disappear quietly.

71
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:49,790
Don't worry. I'll do that.

72
00:09:02,770 --> 00:09:06,950
You want to leave early?  Why, because of what happened earlier?

73
00:09:06,950 --> 00:09:12,150
No.  My uncle is in the hospital, so I want to help with his store.

74
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:18,560
Is that so? Then should we go together?

75
00:09:19,610 --> 00:09:25,610
- Coming with me to our store?
- Yes.  Can't I?

76
00:09:34,620 --> 00:09:36,570
Aunt, I'm here.

77
00:09:36,570 --> 00:09:37,840
Just in time.

78
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:40,790
I was going to call a delivery service, but I can take it.

79
00:09:40,790 --> 00:09:43,320
Will you look after the store for a while?

80
00:09:44,890 --> 00:09:49,220
Hello. The store is beautiful. The flowers are beautiful.

81
00:09:50,410 --> 00:09:53,070
It's hot isn't it? Would you like to see some flowers?

82
00:09:53,070 --> 00:09:55,320
Are you going somewhere?

83
00:09:56,210 --> 00:09:58,800
I was going to make a delivery.

84
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,960
Just make yourself at home.  I can go after you look around.

85
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:04,720
Would you like me to do the delivery with you?

86
00:10:05,690 --> 00:10:07,220
Huh?

87
00:10:16,460 --> 00:10:18,560
The time...

88
00:10:21,650 --> 00:10:25,970
The people receiving them all love it.  Is there anything else left to do?

89
00:10:25,970 --> 00:10:27,950
This is the last one.

90
00:10:27,950 --> 00:10:31,500
Today, I'm taking advantage of you for all the people who ordered flowers.

91
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:34,350
Conductor, would you deliver these flowers too?

92
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:39,730
Gosh. I didn't even say hello properly.  I'm at a loss as to how I will ever repay your unexpected kindness.

93
00:10:39,730 --> 00:10:43,590
If you want to thank me, buy me just one popsicle.

94
00:10:43,590 --> 00:10:45,650
A popsicle?

95
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:53,320
He's young,

96
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:57,530
but he already has a permanent job. His appearance is nice and he is pleasant and doesn't lack in anything.

97
00:10:57,530 --> 00:11:01,230
But, an executive  probably earns a pretty good salary.

98
00:11:01,230 --> 00:11:03,450
How much do you think he earns?

99
00:11:04,370 --> 00:11:05,190
Yi Yeong?

100
00:11:05,190 --> 00:11:07,890
Yi Yeong went to the hospital. Why?

101
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:12,350
A customer is here. Hang up.

102
00:11:14,830 --> 00:11:16,940
Welcome.

103
00:11:18,710 --> 00:11:23,140
Did you hang the sign outside saying you are looking for a part-timer?

104
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:27,030
Yes. For a short term.

105
00:11:27,030 --> 00:11:30,680
It's not retail work, but some manual labor.   For about a month.

106
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:32,530
A month is perfect.

107
00:11:32,530 --> 00:11:36,430
I have a driver's license. I can be on standby from morning until night.

108
00:11:36,430 --> 00:11:39,770
I can do cleaning too.

109
00:11:40,970 --> 00:11:43,160
Come this way, please.

110
00:11:48,430 --> 00:11:50,740
Have you done this kind of work before?

111
00:11:50,740 --> 00:11:51,850
Well...

112
00:11:51,850 --> 00:11:54,760
No matter how much I look at it, it's not just a scratch.

113
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:57,240
I wish you came to the hospital right away.

114
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:59,290
It will heal. It's not even a deep cut.

115
00:11:59,290 --> 00:12:02,120
Aren't you being too picky?

116
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,980
Is it someone else's business? Being so laid back...

117
00:12:04,980 --> 00:12:07,450
- Did you come to see Dad?
- Yeah.

118
00:12:07,450 --> 00:12:12,190
Usually being unable to eat is the hardest part.

119
00:12:12,190 --> 00:12:15,220
So, what do you want to say to me?

120
00:12:29,630 --> 00:12:34,370
I had a knife... and there was blood on my hand...

121
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:38,630
my hands were covered in blood...

122
00:12:39,970 --> 00:12:42,070
That's enough.

123
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:49,600
What are you? Did you rummage through my desk? Did you watch the content?

124
00:12:52,890 --> 00:12:56,920
You really do anything, don't you? Why did you take and watch what you pleased?

125
00:12:56,920 --> 00:13:00,110
You wouldn't even tell me anything.

126
00:13:00,110 --> 00:13:03,160
You keep lying to me.

127
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:06,500
Stupid. This is the consultation process.

128
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:08,710
People are panic-stricken and will do or say anything.

129
00:13:08,710 --> 00:13:10,930
They talk about being abducted by alien beings.

130
00:13:10,930 --> 00:13:13,690
That's why I'm asking.

131
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:19,030
Tell me what you saw and heard.

132
00:13:19,030 --> 00:13:21,850
Tell me everything. Please.

133
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:27,250
I feel like I'm going to die.

134
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:43,070
That day,

135
00:13:44,590 --> 00:13:50,540
I didn't even know you went missing after the Asia Philharmonic concert.

136
00:13:50,540 --> 00:13:53,880
I was working overtime and wasn't even thinking about you.

137
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:58,610
The next morning I got a call from the police.

138
00:13:58,610 --> 00:14:03,010
Your purse and cell phone were found in a car after a hit and run accident.

139
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:05,580
They said they were searching because there was a missing person.

140
00:14:05,580 --> 00:14:10,390
They said they found you on the side of the highway...

141
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,130
She had no major injuries.

142
00:14:13,130 --> 00:14:17,380
When she was discovered, her temperature was low and going down, so it was somehow dangerous.

143
00:14:17,380 --> 00:14:19,700
It rained hard all night.

144
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:22,420
Fortunately, everything is stable now.

145
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:24,610
Thank you.

146
00:14:30,990 --> 00:14:34,170
After three days you regained consciousness.

147
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:40,840
At first you couldn't talk for several days and you were out of your mind.

148
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:44,010
I couldn't see this happening to a person like you.

149
00:14:44,010 --> 00:14:47,600
What happened exactly to you that day?

150
00:14:57,890 --> 00:15:02,770
After you started talking, I recorded our conversations for one month.

151
00:15:02,770 --> 00:15:07,170
What you saw. Although I don't know what you thought about what you saw, these are my conclusions.

152
00:15:07,170 --> 00:15:11,770
It's not that you killed someone. You think you killed someone.

153
00:15:17,460 --> 00:15:20,310
You say I said with my own mouth I killed someone.

154
00:15:20,310 --> 00:15:21,930
You were a patient.

155
00:15:21,930 --> 00:15:25,790
A patient suffering from a serious shock can say anything.

156
00:15:26,890 --> 00:15:28,320
Believe me.

157
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:31,830
I'm someone who makes her living only doing this. I know after the consultations.

158
00:15:31,830 --> 00:15:34,100
You couldn't have killed a person.

159
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:40,420
Moreover, to do that to someone you liked...  Don't you know that about yourself?

160
00:15:43,170 --> 00:15:45,410
Although I'm a doctor, I was so scared too.

161
00:15:45,410 --> 00:15:50,560
You are my little cousin so am I being objective or is that what I want to believe?

162
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:52,670
That's not so.

163
00:15:53,350 --> 00:15:55,770
You did not kill Kim Ian.

164
00:15:55,770 --> 00:16:01,030
You feel guilty. Please trust me and believe in yourself. Huh?

165
00:16:06,710 --> 00:16:08,340
Yeah.

166
00:16:43,740 --> 00:16:46,740
I think I like you, Yun.

167
00:16:47,690 --> 00:16:50,970
Today too I really like you.

168
00:16:50,970 --> 00:16:55,760
Every time you do this, I don't know you well.

169
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:58,760
What do you want from me?

170
00:17:04,420 --> 00:17:07,070
Can I see you for a while? I have something to say.

171
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:11,000
Call me when you get home.

172
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:19,520
- Yes?
-  This is the moving company.

173
00:17:19,520 --> 00:17:23,240
I remember the motel I took that person to.

174
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:25,030
Where is it? I'll go right now.

175
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:29,100
- I'll send you a picture of the vicinity.
- Yes.

176
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:57,500
- Ha Eun Ju?
- Yes.

177
00:17:57,510 --> 00:17:59,380
Please come in.

178
00:18:08,650 --> 00:18:10,570
Welcome.

179
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:40,100
I like hard liquor a bit.

180
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:43,180
I don't like beating around the bush.

181
00:18:43,180 --> 00:18:46,980
Please understand if I just  speak directly.

182
00:18:46,980 --> 00:18:49,260
It's alright, if I can also just speak directly.

183
00:18:49,260 --> 00:18:53,420
After received your call, I found out about you.

184
00:18:53,420 --> 00:18:55,680
That you are a very talented individual.

185
00:18:55,680 --> 00:19:00,180
And that  you have  a reason to meet me. Shall I listen to it?

186
00:19:00,180 --> 00:19:04,530
I heard you are joining the board of directors of the Sinyeong Philharmonic.

187
00:19:04,530 --> 00:19:05,830
So?

188
00:19:05,830 --> 00:19:07,760
I need a shoulder to lean on.

189
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:11,350
I don't want to quit my job.

190
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:19,350
Professor Kang Myeong Seok of Sinyeong Music College is someone you know.

191
00:19:20,080 --> 00:19:21,850
He fired me as of yesterday.

192
00:19:21,850 --> 00:19:26,690
The rumor isn't very nice. Do I look like a pushover?

193
00:19:26,690 --> 00:19:31,450
I approached a very rich man and he bought me an instrument?

194
00:19:31,450 --> 00:19:35,830
It's half right. It wasn't me. He approached me.

195
00:19:35,830 --> 00:19:39,310
The instrument too. He bought it for me.

196
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:46,140
I wish I hadn't accepted it, but when I saw the violin in front of me,

197
00:19:46,140 --> 00:19:49,520
I absolutely just couldn't let it go.

198
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:54,080
My bad, right. I also couldn't do anything about the nasty rumor.

199
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:58,100
Just exactly what do you want from me?

200
00:19:58,100 --> 00:20:00,000
The stage.

201
00:20:00,770 --> 00:20:05,810
I want to be in a position where no one can touch me.   No one.

202
00:20:05,810 --> 00:20:07,410
I'm talented. I am skilled too.

203
00:20:07,410 --> 00:20:12,380
I'm bitten by the practice bug and I'm earnest.

204
00:20:15,030 --> 00:20:17,880
What can you give me?

205
00:20:19,430 --> 00:20:21,540
Your son.

206
00:20:22,270 --> 00:20:28,120
Jang Yun, or rather... Jang Do Hun.

207
00:20:28,880 --> 00:20:31,790
I'll get him to leave our orchestra.

208
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:04,260
Another who came for me?

209
00:21:04,260 --> 00:21:06,380
It's been a long time.

210
00:21:08,790 --> 00:21:12,780
Why did the young master of that noble house come all the way here?

211
00:21:13,570 --> 00:21:19,230
Come to think of it, you threw me into prison without me even receiving an agreement.

212
00:21:20,060 --> 00:21:23,520
How much I suffered for a year.

213
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:29,320
Stop talking nonsense and answer my question. What is the object you're searching for?

214
00:21:31,330 --> 00:21:33,960
Our Young Master seems to be in a big rush.

215
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:37,500
Your question is wrong, Jang Do Hun.

216
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:40,700
You need to ask first,  "Did you murder my brother?"

217
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:42,170
Isn't that so?

218
00:21:42,170 --> 00:21:43,880
You're the one who killed him.

219
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:45,620
You pushed his car making it look like a hit-and-run.

220
00:21:45,620 --> 00:21:47,620
Deng!

221
00:21:47,620 --> 00:21:50,440
You're wrong. It's not me.

222
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:54,040
I've already been to prison so why would I lie?

223
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:56,230
If it's not you,

224
00:21:56,230 --> 00:21:58,650
then who? Who killed him? Why?

225
00:21:58,650 --> 00:22:00,940
Who is behind you?

226
00:22:02,510 --> 00:22:04,540
People are so dumb.

227
00:22:04,540 --> 00:22:08,990
The answer is close by. Why can't you find it and are asking someone like me?

228
00:22:08,990 --> 00:22:10,950
Close?

229
00:22:10,950 --> 00:22:12,030
Someone close?

230
00:22:12,030 --> 00:22:14,640
Someone you know.

231
00:22:21,760 --> 00:22:25,230
What is the object you are looking for?

232
00:22:25,230 --> 00:22:28,430
It's something the higher-ups want to find at any cost.

233
00:22:28,430 --> 00:22:33,980
They are even killing people for it. So, don't you think you shouldn't be wandering around outside?

234
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:36,920
Can't you get your head around that?

235
00:22:36,920 --> 00:22:39,950
Who is it and what is it!  Tell me everything you know!

236
00:22:39,950 --> 00:22:44,390
Why should I? That's no fun.

237
00:22:44,390 --> 00:22:47,370
I am also risking my life.

238
00:23:00,180 --> 00:23:03,600
How much are you getting paid for this work?  If it's money, I can give it  to you.

239
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:06,330
Well then, 3 billion won.

240
00:23:06,330 --> 00:23:10,220
Just as much as to make a person the happiest.

241
00:23:10,220 --> 00:23:15,310
According to the news. Can you give it to me? If you give it me, Ill tell you everything I know.

242
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:22,110
Ah, come to think of it, was that woman there?

243
00:23:22,110 --> 00:23:24,030
Hong Yi Yeong.

244
00:23:24,950 --> 00:23:28,300
She might have the object.

245
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:33,310
But then her memory flits here and there.

246
00:23:33,310 --> 00:23:36,380
It's a shame.

247
00:23:37,910 --> 00:23:41,420
Leave that woman alone. Don't touch her.

248
00:23:42,340 --> 00:23:45,570
Why? What is that woman hiding?

249
00:23:45,570 --> 00:23:51,410
On that day she stabbed your brother with a knife.

250
00:23:51,410 --> 00:23:54,080
Did I see everything?

251
00:23:55,330 --> 00:23:57,840
Oh right. You two are dating.

252
00:23:57,840 --> 00:24:00,740
You've been going in and out of each other's homes.

253
00:24:00,740 --> 00:24:04,440
Yesterday morning I also saw her come out of your house.

254
00:24:04,440 --> 00:24:07,900
Are  you watching her even while you two are sleeping together?

255
00:24:13,330 --> 00:24:15,770
Why, are you going to kill me?

256
00:24:15,770 --> 00:24:17,440
Please kill me.

257
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:20,020
Kill me. Kill me.

258
00:24:20,020 --> 00:24:22,400
I said to kill me.

259
00:24:49,750 --> 00:24:52,410
Tone-Deaf

260
00:24:53,790 --> 00:24:55,450
Hello?

261
00:24:55,450 --> 00:24:57,230
It's me.

262
00:24:58,550 --> 00:25:01,450
Can I see you for a little while?

263
00:25:01,450 --> 00:25:04,420
What's wrong with your voice? Did something happen?

264
00:25:04,420 --> 00:25:07,410
No. Nothing happened.

265
00:25:08,110 --> 00:25:13,340
Just... just.

266
00:25:16,050 --> 00:25:18,670
I want to see you.

267
00:25:18,670 --> 00:25:23,610
I just got off a taxi.  I'll wait for you at the convenience store.

268
00:25:51,970 --> 00:25:58,950
